('8057','120','1','6','don-t-get-surgery-on-a-friday.html','Dont get surgery on a Friday',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<p>If you have any say, you might want to avoid scheduling your next surgery on a Friday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most comprehensive analysis of what happens to patients who have surgery on Fridays versus Mondays, published this month in&nbsp;<em>JAMA</em>&nbsp;by more than a dozen US and Canadian researchers, is unequivocal: The people who underwent all kinds of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamanetworkopen/fullarticle/2830842\">procedures before the weekend suffered</a>&nbsp;on average more short-term, medium-term, and long-term complications than people who went under the knife after the weekend was over.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The study was based in Ontario and included more than 450,000 patients who received one of the 25 most common surgeries between 2007 and 2019.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2017/10/31/16566450/bernie-sanders-canada-health-care\">Canada&rsquo;s universal health care program</a>&nbsp;allowed the researchers to more easily track patients over time and it eliminated finances as a variable in how patients fared.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Previous studies have generally found the same effects across different types of health systems: One&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vox.com/2020/1/28/21074386/health-care-rationing-britain-nhs-nice-medicare-for-all\">UK</a>-based study had reported&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bmj.com/content/346/bmj.f2424\">better outcomes for Monday surgeries</a>&nbsp;after 30 days. A paper looking at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2020/1/17/21046874/netherlands-universal-health-insurance-private\">Dutch patients</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26150550/\">detected higher mortality rates</a>&nbsp;after one month for patients who had Friday surgeries compared to Monday. This appears to be a phenomenon no matter the country, as prior&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oce.ovid.com/article/00007719-201508000-00026\">US-based research</a>&nbsp;also attests.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The new study covered all surgery specialties &mdash; including orthopedic surgery, vascular surgery, and obstetrics &mdash; and followed patients&rsquo; outcomes at 30 days, 90 days and one year. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://cdn.jamanetwork.com/ama/content_public/journal/jamanetworkopen/939562/zoi241642supp1_prod_1740155894.63922.pdf?Expires=1745396035&amp;Signature=4P8tbsgf2RL1BAxy5H6Cf86gtCW67Oa94xHr9QR4ebEcE6XuujlZg0a7TR3xXi~f9rCtaWQ5rQeWVlgf-3vQREvQ~XTG3W0YqgeNNLYFXP6qbssnyR-fWPXnXoBHZrfQ8Ofe06zweKGVgbvV0vhO0BEnWq~e~zXfB~8iBM2M3b6U2OfZUWw9QtrKdrjGF1u8lVWGCnmYhNxHwS10a70ymg3F11iuIA6kad3QIDC0uh053MUa97AIUOFLMXrNdBQb3gXwr5l2UsTDZD9N1G8B3BsCZkLo6oXkjRGVEvdNo8AwAEpC52nM43b6Teo2I1UKBhyX2dcxMXF9T1EQ2IXwsg__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAIE5G5CRDK6RD3PGA\">study tracked whether patients died</a>, were readmitted to the hospital, or experienced any other complications, like an infection, for example, during their hospital stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who received pre-weekend surgeries &mdash; defined as a Friday or a Thursday before a long weekend &mdash; were overall about 5 percent more likely to experience one of those complications within a year of their surgery than people who got post-weekend procedures (on Monday or the Tuesday after a long weekend). The effect was stronger for heart and vascular surgeries; it was negligible for obstetric and plastic surgeries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a data-pswp-height=\"1240\" data-pswp-width=\"1240\" href=\"https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0,1.4866979655712,100,97.026604068858\" rel=\"noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Pre-weekend surgeries have more complications than post-weekend surgeries\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" data-nimg=\"fill\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" src=\"https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=2400\" srcset=\"https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=256 256w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=376 376w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=384 384w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=415 415w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=480 480w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=540 540w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=640 640w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=750 750w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=828 828w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=1080 1080w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=1200 1200w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=1440 1440w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.vox.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/03/p8b8M-pre-weekend-surgeries-have-more-complications-than-post-weekend-surgeries.png?quality=90&amp;strip=all&amp;crop=0%2C1.4866979655712%2C100%2C97.026604068858&amp;w=2400 2400w\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There could be a few things going on here, according to the researchers&rsquo; analysis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Researchers found Friday surgeries were more likely to be performed by junior surgeons when compared to Monday surgeries. &ldquo;This difference in expertise may play a role in the observed differences in outcomes,&rdquo; they wrote, based on a statistical analysis that controlled for other factors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There could also be fewer senior colleagues on the hospital campus for the junior physicians to consult with, the authors said. In addition, the weekend doctors and nurses may be less familiar with the patient&rsquo;s case, raising the risk that complications will be caught later and therefore lead to worse outcomes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is common for hospitals to have fewer doctors and nurses working the weekends and those who do work tend to be less experienced, which could likewise help explain the study&rsquo;s findings, said Betty Rambur, a nursing professor at the University of Rhode Island.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;The combination of fewer staff and less experienced staff certainly can contribute to poor patient outcomes,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The findings should motivate hospital executives to rethink how they are staffing their wards on Fridays and over the weekend, to avoid complications that put surgery patients in danger.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course, this is also useful information for any of us who need elective surgery at any point in the future. When we&rsquo;re able to plan ahead for a procedure &mdash; whether&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.urmc.rochester.edu/news/publications/health-matters/why-vasectomies-surge-during-march-madness\">a vasectomy carefully timed to coincide with March Madness</a>&nbsp;or a knee replacement or whatever &mdash; it&rsquo;s worth trying to find a time slot earlier in the week.</p>\r\n','Dont get surgery on a Friday','','','75','1','0',NULL,'1','1_wrED-dIfuHiOhR-RMyVZTw_67e1e470a605b.jpg','0','1',NULL,NULL,'1','0','0','1','2025-03-25 04:02:36','2025-03-25 04:19:47','0','2000-01-27 00:00:00.0000','0'),
('8058','120','1','6','study-reveals-friday-surgeries-linked-to-12-higher-death-risk-than-early-week-operations.html','Study Reveals Friday Surgeries Linked To 12% Higher Death Risk Than Early Week Operations',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3 data-end=\"68\" data-start=\"0\"><strong data-end=\"68\" data-start=\"4\">Friday Surgeries are a Riskier Choice for Patients Study Finds</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"525\" data-start=\"70\">A recent study has revealed surgeries performed on Fridays carry a 12% high risk of death compared to the surgeries done earlier in the week. This finding has prompted healthcare professionals to rethink their timing of surgical procedures, as the day of the week could play a significant role in post operative survival rates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"1139\" data-start=\"611\">A major finding from this study is that patients who undergo surgery on Fridays are at a significantly higher risk of death. The research, which analyzed data from hospitals in Ontario, Canada, showed that individuals who had surgeries just before the weekend faced a higher risk of death at 30 days (9% increase), 90 days (10%), and one year (12%) compared to surgeries performed after the weekend.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 data-end=\"2114\" data-start=\"2073\"><strong data-end=\"2114\" data-start=\"2077\">Why Are Friday Surgeries Riskier?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"2462\" data-start=\"2116\">several factors contribute to the increased risk with Friday surgeries. One of the most effective risks are &ldquo;staff fatigue&rdquo;. Surgeons and medical professionals are tired after a long week of back to back surgeries, which can affect their concentration and performance on fridays. This could lead to increased chances of complications during and after surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"2760\" data-start=\"2464\">Another factor is &ldquo;hospital resources&rdquo;. Many hospitals operate on a decreased capacity during the weekends, with fewer staff and fewer specialists available. If patients require emergency care or a consult from a senior doctor, it may not be as readily accessible on Friday evenings and weekends.</p>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"3070\" data-start=\"2762\">Last, the &ldquo;weekend effect&rdquo; plays a huge role. The weekend effect refers to the event where hospitals, particularly those with fewer resources or less staffing, may struggle to provide timely post-surgical monitoring. This gap in care can add to the risks associated with surgery and recovery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"3455\" data-start=\"3180\">Several factors, including staff fatigue, reduced hospital staffing, and fewer available resources, contribute to the increased risks of Friday surgeries. Medical staff might be tired after a busy week, and the weekend staffing shortage can delay post-operative care.</p>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"3832\" data-start=\"3524\">While it&rsquo;s not always possible to choose the timing of a surgery, patients concerned about the risks associated with Friday surgeries should discuss their options with their healthcare providers. Surgeons can offer advice on the optimal timing of procedures based on the patient&rsquo;s condition and surgery type.</p>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"3832\" data-start=\"3524\"><a aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" aria-label=\"View full size photo\" href=\"https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy.jpg\"><img alt=\"a person in a hospital bed with an iv\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" height=\"274\" sizes=\"(max-width: 411px) 100vw, 411px\" src=\"https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy-600x400.jpg\" srcset=\"https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy-600x400.jpg 600w, https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy-768x512.jpg 768w, https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy-300x200.jpg 300w, https://esteemstream.news/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/zqemeab-wpy.jpg 1600w\" width=\"411\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 data-end=\"4291\" data-start=\"4246\"><strong data-end=\"4291\" data-start=\"4250\">Conclusion</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p data-end=\"4796\" data-start=\"4293\">The timing of surgical procedures plays a significant role in patient outcomes. The study&rsquo;s findings indicate that Friday surgeries are associated with a 12% higher mortality rate than those performed earlier in the week. Factors like staff fatigue, limited resources, and the weekend effect contribute to this increased risk. As healthcare providers continue to explore these correlations, there is a push to consider how surgical schedules can be improved for better patient outcomes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Related stories:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://interestingengineering.com/health/friday-surgeries-higher-death-risk\">https://interestingengineering.com/health/friday-surgeries-higher-death-risk</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://medicalxpress.com/news/2025-03-weekends-affect-surgical-outcomes.html\">https://medicalxpress.com/news/2025-03-weekends-affect-surgical-outcomes.html</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.vice.com/en/article/youre-more-likely-to-die-if-you-have-surgery-on-a-friday/\">https://www.vice.com/en/article/youre-more-likely-to-die-if-you-have-surgery-on-a-friday/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://medicalxpress.com/news/2025-03-surgery-weekend-bad-idea.html\">https://medicalxpress.com/news/2025-03-surgery-weekend-bad-idea.html</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.iflscience.com/dont-have-surgery-on-a-friday-youre-more-likely-to-die-study-shows-78334\">https://www.iflscience.com/dont-have-surgery-on-a-friday-youre-more-likely-to-die-study-shows-78334</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Take Action:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.sciencealert.com/having-surgery-at-the-end-of-the-week-could-make-a-concerning-difference\">https://www.sciencealert.com/having-surgery-at-the-end-of-the-week-could-make-a-concerning-difference</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://advisory.com/daily-briefing/2025/03/10/weekend-effect\">https://advisory.com/daily-briefing/2025/03/10/weekend-effect</a></p>\r\n','Study Reveals Friday Surgeries Linked To 12% Higher Death Risk Than Early Week Operations','','','93','1','0',NULL,'1','zqemeab-wpy_67e1eae436eb9.jpg','0','1',NULL,NULL,'1','0','0','1','2025-03-25 04:29:54','2025-03-25 04:39:36','0','2000-01-27 00:00:00.0000','0'),
